The gas drilling expedition on Lamuâ€™s Pate Island received a boost after a long-awaited rig arrived from Tunisia on Thursday. Speaking to the Nation, Zarara Oil and Gas Ltd Country Manager Peter Nduru said the rig had arrived in Mombasa early this week and was transported to Lamu by ship. He said the rig is currently at Manda Bay near the site of the Lamu Port South Sudan Ethiopia Transport corridor. He said the equipment will be ferried to Pate Island on Friday. Mr Nduru said the new rig will enable the firm to continue drilling up to 4,500m down in search of the gas.  